<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-10-19.0.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa1019.htm">Written Answers Tuesday 19 October 2010</major-heading>

<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-10-19.1.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa1019.htm">Scottish Executive</major-heading>

<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-10-19.S3W-34218.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa1019.htm#1">Finance</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-10-19.S3W-34218.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80359" speakername="Michael McMahon (Hamilton North and Bellshill) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34218" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa1019.htm#1" holdingdate="2010-06-21">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what the total cost has been of supporting the work of the Council of Economic Advisers, including travel and hotel costs.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-10-19.S3W-34218.r0" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa1019.htm#MinisterName">

  <p><a name="MinisterName" id="MinisterName"></a><strong>John Swinney: </strong>The costs associated with each Council of Economic Advisers meeting, and supplementary meetings, are routinely published on the Scottish Government website at:</p>

  <p><a href="http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Topics/Economy/Council-Economic-Advisers/disclosures" target="_blank">http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Topics/Economy/Council-Economic-Advisers/disclosures</a>.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-10-19.S3W-35972.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa1019.htm#2">Scottish Government Staff</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-10-19.S3W-35972.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80281" speakername="Ms Wendy Alexander (Paisley North) (Lab)" spid="S3W-35972" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa1019.htm#2" holdingdate="2010-09-27">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how many employees of it and its agencies are paid (a) &pound;100,000 to &pound;150,000, (b) &pound;150,001 to &pound;200,000 and (c) more than &pound;200,000.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-10-19.S3W-35972.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80397" speakername="John Swinney" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa1019.htm#2">

  <p>There are currently 20 permanent employees* of the Scottish Government and associated agencies who are paid an annual basic salary of above &pound;100,000. These are split into the following salary brackets:-</p>

  <p>(a) 17 people currently paid between &pound;100,000 and &pound;150,000;</p>

  <p>(b) three people currently paid between &pound;150,001 and &pound;200,000; and</p>

  <p>(c) none paid more than &pound;200,000.</p>

  <p>The list of 172 senior civil servants in central government departments and senior staff in non departmental public bodies who earn more than &pound;150,000 each year was published on the Cabinet Office website on 31 May 2010. Details are available at:</p>

  <p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20100713194045/http://www.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/newsroom/news_releases/2010/100701-quangos.aspx" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20100713194045/http://www.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/newsroom/<br /> news_releases/2010/100701-quangos.aspx</a></p>

  <p>Note: *excludes employees on outward loan/secondment</p>

</reply>
